setups:

Install Driver
1. Download K80 driver: http://www.nvidia.com/download/driverResults.aspx/124729/en-us
2. sudo dpkg -i <the driver file you just downloaded>.deb
3. sudo apt-get update
4. sudo apt-get install cuda-drivers
5. reboot

Install CUDA:
1. download CUDA: https://developer.nvidia.com/cuda-downloads?target_os=Linux&target_arch=x86_64&target_distro=Ubuntu&target_version=1604&target_type=runfilelocal
2. sudo sh <cuda you just downloaded>.run --override

Install CuDNN:
1. Download CuDNN (need Nvidia account)
2. follow the instructions from official website

Install Python3

Install PyTorch

Install Jupyter notebook

Start Jupyter Server
http://jupyter-notebook.readthedocs.io/en/stable/public_server.html

Install Visdom

Start Visdom Server

Install kaggle-cli
1. pip install kaggle-cli
2. kg download -u <username> -p <password> -c cdiscount-image-classification-challenge
